{% if not custom_methodology %}
## Tiered workflow

| Tier | Meaning | Review |
|------|---------|--------|
| **S** | Schema, security, infra, migrations, auth, deploy | Human |
| **A** | New feature surface (endpoints, services, integrations) | Human |
| **B** | Enhancement to existing behavior | Auto-merge if CI green |
| **C** | Trivial (docs, comments, typos in non-code) | Auto-merge if CI green |

All tiers: branch, PR, tests, lint, security. **Conventional commits:** `feat|fix|docs|refactor|test|chore|ci|perf: description`

{% endif %}
{% if not custom_methodology %}
## Guardrails

**NEVER:** Drop DB/schema; delete infra (CI workflows, deploy, `batten`, `batten.yml`); push to main; skip tests; secrets in code; `allow_origins=["*"]`; destructive SQL without a plan; TODO/FIXME/HACK in commits; ghost code; bare `except`/silenced errors; dependencies without CVE check.

**ALWAYS:** Tests before and after; update `.github/context/` when architecture/API/modules change; parameterized SQL; delegate heavy work to sub-agents; API-first; OWASP; validate inputs at boundaries; verify imports; functions under 50 lines; match file style; prefer editing existing files.

Full detail: `.github/instructions/guardrails.md`
{% endif %}
